<org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription xmi:version="2.0" xmlns:xmi="http://www.omg.org/XMI" xmlns:org.eclipse.epf.uma="http://www.eclipse.org/epf/uma/1.0.6/uma.ecore" xmlns:epf="http://www.eclipse.org/epf" epf:version="1.5.1" xmlns:rmc="http://www.ibm.com/rmc" rmc:version="7.5.1" xmi:id="-EGQsGti2C8qkC1JGhIMEOQ" name=",_TG-aAA9WEd6LqqyVYr5Pow" guid="-EGQsGti2C8qkC1JGhIMEOQ" changeDate="2009-05-19T08:30:51.227-0700" version="7.5.0">
  <mainDescription>&lt;p> This is the task where all qualified components are assigned to a specific &#xD;
  work&amp;nbsp;pipeline to be evaluated, selected, and prioritized.&amp;nbsp;These can &#xD;
  be among the work&amp;nbsp;pipelines: &lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Production support&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Application maintenance&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &#xD;
  &lt;li> Strategic projects&lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;p> Each&amp;nbsp;pipeline represents work of a different type and&amp;nbsp;contains components &#xD;
  that share common characteristics. Moreover, each&amp;nbsp;pipeline is aligned with &#xD;
  the organization's strategic planning process and is regulated by a predefined &#xD;
  set of criteria and metrics. &lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p> Work of different types warrant different levels of process and controls. &#xD;
  For example, the data definition requirement for a support request differs from &#xD;
  that of a strategic project. &lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Re-categorize components as needed during the process, as more knowledge is built around&amp;nbsp;each component.&#xD;
&lt;/p></mainDescription>
  <purpose>To ensure that components are processed in a consistent manner, using processes &#xD;
and techniques adapted to&amp;nbsp;a particular work pipeline, so that portfolio-level &#xD;
balancing metrics and targets can be applied.</purpose>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription>
